description:
### UniqueDigitProducts

A problem that takes in an array of integers and returns the count of product of the digits of the integers after making each digit of the integer unique.

Input: An array of integers (1 <= a.length <= 50; 1 <= a[i] <= 10^9)
Output: Returns a count of unique products.

Example:

``` uniqueDigitProducts([2, 8, 121, 42, 222, 23]) // 3 ```
